      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>This patient has <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"rZbf1H\">viral rhinosinusitis</a> and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>does not require additional diagnostic evaluation</b></span>. Distinguishing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"rZbf1H\">viral rhinosinusitis</a> from bacterial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tF0XP3&anker=Z20ffbe5edb7667e7ff0930a27b0d0d14\" data-learningcard-id=\"tF0XP3\" data-anker=\"Z20ffbe5edb7667e7ff0930a27b0d0d14\" data-sememe-id=\"1vb2_v\">upper respiratory infections</a>, especially <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"7Zb41H\">acute bacterial sinusitis</a>, is important, to avoid unnecessary administration of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a>. Nasal secretions often change color after a few days and may turn yellow, but this does not imply bacterial <span data-sememe-id=\"_f15KT0\">superinfection</span>. This patient’s symptoms are not consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"7Zb41H\">acute bacterial sinusitis</a>: They have lasted &lt;10 days, are mild to moderate in severity, and are improving.<br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Z7458c2b9899d21977fa87a8dae1b623d\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"rZbf1H\">Viral rhinosinusitis</a> is often caused by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z2f41366afe9d070a6c0fb766f97b50a9\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z2f41366afe9d070a6c0fb766f97b50a9\" data-section-id=\"fackPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"DOY1u6\">rhinoviruses</a>, although other <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-section-id=\"VacGja0\">viruses</a> such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"qkYCK6\">respiratory syncytial virus</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z30cf1c844b0e42bed39f00950cf3a137\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"qkYCK6\">RSV</a>), <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zc9fd2c044745d5b6f6ef5fe6293d10c5\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zc9fd2c044745d5b6f6ef5fe6293d10c5\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\" data-sememe-id=\"SOYy76\">coronavirus</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Z1123d8bb56e5d009270ba5ccbde98478\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Z1123d8bb56e5d009270ba5ccbde98478\" data-section-id=\"2acTPa0\">human metapneumovirus</a> have also been implicated. These <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Pn0Wtg&anker=Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Pn0Wtg\" data-anker=\"Zcdc83877f75d9d9b9a07ece6544f646c\" data-section-id=\"VacGja0\">viruses</a> are transmitted from person to person via respiratory droplets. Symptoms usually resolve after 10 to 14 days, and specific diagnostic tests are generally not required. Treatment consists of supportive care.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> Although nasal discharge can become yellow and thick during a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gs0Bwh&anker=Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gs0Bwh\" data-anker=\"Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-sememe-id=\"FKWgRm0\">common cold</a>, an important clue to distinguish a cold from a bacterial respiratory infection is overall clinical improvement in mild-to-moderate respiratory symptoms within 10 to 14 days after their onset.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"kzbmGw\">Allergy</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> testing is part of the workup for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mq0V_S&anker=Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-learningcard-id=\"mq0V_S\" data-anker=\"Zb83250e306f9a49d8735d86bc7695174\" data-sememe-id=\"21aTTj\">allergic rhinitis</a>, which usually manifests with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cp0aoS&anker=Z25c693a94290e2fb49a324337c7a38cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"cp0aoS\" data-anker=\"Z25c693a94290e2fb49a324337c7a38cb\" data-section-id=\"XDc91e0\" data-sememe-id=\"hFXc3-\">conjunctival</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a>, itchy eyes, nasal discharge, and congestion that fail to resolve after 10 to 14 days unless the offending agent is removed.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Chest imaging, most often <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S80yN3&anker=Z2b7edf3ee0203011545786467a61cbd8\" data-learningcard-id=\"S80yN3\" data-anker=\"Z2b7edf3ee0203011545786467a61cbd8\" data-sememe-id=\"SeXyyC\">chest radiography</a>, is part of the evaluation for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a>, which usually manifests with a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> that produces mucopurulent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tl0XAT&anker=Z893a8c8ecb23b11a8df0179f03b62956\" data-learningcard-id=\"tl0XAT\" data-anker=\"Z893a8c8ecb23b11a8df0179f03b62956\" data-section-id=\"sCXttZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"oaY0ln\">sputum</a>, high-grade <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Yo0n0S&anker=Z51972b7151425356fc29cc17fb9e3011\" data-learningcard-id=\"Yo0n0S\" data-anker=\"Z51972b7151425356fc29cc17fb9e3011\" data-section-id=\"KicUsX0\" data-sememe-id=\"D_c1qU0\">pleuritic chest pain</a>. This patient’s constellation of symptoms does not suggest <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>A pharyngeal swab for group A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Sn0ysg&anker=Zc55380d620c82ec8d6a1edfc63b9bfbf\" data-learningcard-id=\"Sn0ysg\" data-anker=\"Zc55380d620c82ec8d6a1edfc63b9bfbf\" data-section-id=\"r0cfha0\" data-sememe-id=\"FQYgBK\">streptococcus</a> is part of the workup for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=wj0hcT&anker=Zd78ca280c011c24412c3208144928626\" data-learningcard-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-anker=\"Zd78ca280c011c24412c3208144928626\" data-section-id=\"CkYqJ6\" data-sememe-id=\"vo1Ad30\">acute bacterial pharyngitis</a>, which is characterized by enlarged <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=960NMS&anker=Za1bfe57362661c687aedbf6e279b7905\" data-learningcard-id=\"960NMS\" data-anker=\"Za1bfe57362661c687aedbf6e279b7905\" data-section-id=\"ZEcZ8V0\">tonsils</a> (often with an associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"vIYAeq\">purulent</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"gbaFGQ\">exudate</span>), tender <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=do0oaS&anker=Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\" data-learningcard-id=\"do0oaS\" data-anker=\"Zd683b39cdd22e209ef414f798da53d44\">cervical lymphadenopathy</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, and the absence of other respiratory symptoms. This patient has none of these signs or symptoms.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Sinus imaging is recommended for cases of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"7Zb41H\">acute bacterial sinusitis</a> that do not respond to <span data-sememe-id=\"7WW4540\">broad-spectrum antibiotics</span>. The following clinical presentations that should raise suspicion for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"7Zb41H\">acute bacterial sinusitis</a>: persistent symptoms of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zcb51da2091237759c0cda1c4047431bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zcb51da2091237759c0cda1c4047431bb\" data-section-id=\"R4YlQ6\" data-sememe-id=\"a1aQ2j\">acute rhinosinusitis</a> for 10 or more days with no signs of improvement, early onset of severe symptoms, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"vIYAeq\">purulent</a> nasal secretion or facial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> ≥38.0°C, that last more than 3 to 4 days, or clinical worsening with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"vIYAeq\">purulent</a> nasal secretions after initial improvement of respiratory symptoms. This patient’s symptoms are not consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sj0tbT&anker=Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-learningcard-id=\"sj0tbT\" data-anker=\"Zbaff380264f76878d466a67dcb227a78\" data-section-id=\"44Y3j6\" data-sememe-id=\"7Zb41H\">acute bacterial sinusitis</a>: They have lasted &lt;10 days, are mild to moderate in severity, and are improving.</div>",
      "hint": "Otherwise known as the common cold, viral rhinosinusitis is characterized by an initial presentation of sore throat, headache, and low-grade fever followed by rhinorrhea, nasal congestion, and dry cough.",
