      "text": "A 32-year-old woman presents with a 4-day history of runny nose, nasal congestion, sneezing, and dry cough. She reports mild sore throat and fatigue but denies fever, chills, or shortness of breath. Vital signs are normal, and physical examination shows clear nasal discharge, mild throat erythema, and clear lung sounds bilaterally. Her symptoms have been stable for the past 2 days. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
