      "text": "A 28-year-old patient presents with a 5-day history of rhinorrhea and nasal congestion. The patient reports initial improvement on day 3 but developed worsening cough, increased fatigue, and subjective fever yesterday. Vital signs are BP, 120/75; P, 98; R, 18; T, 38.4°C (101.1°F); oxygen saturation, 97% on room air. Physical examination shows clear nasal discharge, no sinus tenderness, and crackles in the left lower lung field. What is the most appropriate next step?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Obtain chest x-ray"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Order influenza rapid antigen test"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Prescribe amoxicillin/clavulanate"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Prescribe oral prednisone"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Discharge with symptomatic treatment"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient's biphasic course with initial improvement followed by worsening <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, and fatigue in combination with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tl0XAT&anker=Z663ed2d3cd3880ca59f2d48341661e66\" data-learningcard-id=\"tl0XAT\" data-anker=\"Z663ed2d3cd3880ca59f2d48341661e66\" data-section-id=\"8CXOFZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"vQbABt\">crackles</a> on <span data-sememe-id=\"8V1Owf0\">auscultation</span> suggests secondary bacterial infection. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S80yN3&anker=Z2b7edf3ee0203011545786467a61cbd8\" data-learningcard-id=\"S80yN3\" data-anker=\"Z2b7edf3ee0203011545786467a61cbd8\" data-sememe-id=\"SeXyyC\">Chest x-ray</a> is specifically indicated is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a> is suspected as a complication of a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gs0Bwh&anker=Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gs0Bwh\" data-anker=\"Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-sememe-id=\"FKWgRm0\">common cold</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Viral detection techniques including <span data-sememe-id=\"JHcsrd0\">rapid antigen tests</span> are not routinely recommended for diagnosing a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gs0Bwh&anker=Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gs0Bwh\" data-anker=\"Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-sememe-id=\"FKWgRm0\">common cold</a>. This patient's clinical presentation is consistent with viral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tF0XP3&anker=Z20ffbe5edb7667e7ff0930a27b0d0d14\" data-learningcard-id=\"tF0XP3\" data-anker=\"Z20ffbe5edb7667e7ff0930a27b0d0d14\" data-sememe-id=\"1vb2_v\">upper respiratory infection</a>, but the priority is evaluating for bacterial complications.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">Antibiotics</a> should not be prescribed without evidence of bacterial infection. Diagnostic evaluation should be performed before <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-section-id=\"cubaJv\" data-sememe-id=\"yOadEk\">empiric antibiotic therapy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">Corticosteroids</a> are not indicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Gs0Bwh&anker=Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Gs0Bwh\" data-anker=\"Z828b1ca99b33821e1a4cd147fc26350a\" data-sememe-id=\"FKWgRm0\">common cold</a> treatment. While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">corticosteroids</a> are used in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z9c4ceb1bccafed48699943dc55986c90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z9c4ceb1bccafed48699943dc55986c90\" data-section-id=\"pUaLVP\">treatment of pneumonia</a>, they are typically only indicated in severe presentations, and the diagnosis must first be confirmed.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>This patient's biphasic illness pattern with initial improvement followed by worsening symptoms raises concern for secondary bacterial infection, particularly <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z36f83311c3582932defdae7a73e5730b\" data-sememe-id=\"rk0f6T\">pneumonia</a>, which requires evaluation before discharge.</div>",
